Key Match Events: Shohei Ohtani hit a tying home run in the ninth inning.
Mookie Betts hit a game-ending drive as the Los Angeles Dodgers rallied for a 6-5 victory.
Ohtani had four hits and added two stolen bases, giving him 53 home runs and 55 steals on the season.
Betts hit a walk-off homer to left field on a 101-mph sinker from Halvorsen for his 19th on the season.
Five Los Angeles pitchers combined for a season-high 17 strikeouts.
Blake Treinen struck out the side in the ninth inning.
Post-Match Reflections: Dodgers manager Dave Roberts praised Shohei Ohtani's performance, stating he hasn't seen a player as locked in as Ohtani in quite some time.
Mookie Betts expressed the importance of the win, especially after seeing that San Diego won their game.
Betts commented on the upcoming series against the Padres, highlighting the energy and emotions expected in those games.
